    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> It means that when reading from a url, then the configure parameters must be extracted and passed through the props.\r\n\r\nDo we have an example on how to do that?\r\n\r\n@zackify what do you think? We believe it's tricky to have a Configure widget that read both ways (from props, from state).\r\n\r\nWhen it reads from both props and state, which one should take precedence? @mthuret Can you maybe precise exactly what were the struggles trying to support it both ways?",
