    "body": "Sorry that wasn't explained well. On mount, take from existing state. Any\ntime componentWillReceiveProps is called, that takes precedence.\nOn Fri, Feb 10, 2017 at 19:33 Zach Silveira <zackify@gmail.com> wrote:\n\n> I see the problem. Take from props if the props are null in\n> componentWillReceiveProps. On initial mount take from the state if it\n> doesn't exist then try getting from the props? That might fix it\n> On Fri, Feb 10, 2017 at 19:03 Vincent Voyer <notifications@github.com>\n> wrote:\n>\n> It means that when reading from a url, then the configure parameters must\n> be extracted and passed through the props.\n>\n> Do we have an example on how to do that?\n>\n> @zackify <https://github.com/zackify> what do you think? We believe it's\n> tricky to have a Configure widget that read both ways (from props, from\n> state).\n>\n> When it reads from both props and state, which one should take precedence?\n> @mthuret <https://github.com/mthuret> Can you maybe precise exactly what\n> were the struggles trying to support it both ways?\n>\n> —\n> You are receiving this because you were mentioned.\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub\n> <https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/1967#issuecomment-279099649>,\n> or mute the thread\n> <https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AAbacDc62eMRCKNHSLV_qtNx0wZrwpl1ks5rbPq1gaJpZM4L9lO5>\n> .\n>\n>\n",
